The paper discusses the design and implementation of smart contracts, which are relevant to the fields of cryptography (cs.CR), distributed computing (cs.DC), software engineering (cs.SE), deep learning (cs.DL), and programming languages (cs.PL). However, since the paper focuses on the analysis of smart contract platforms and programming patterns, we can assume that the most relevant categories are cs.CR and cs.DC, followed by cs.SE, cs.DL, and cs.PL.
